VALUES ('7ec6dbbf-03b5-4ee4-aea7-f651d03b5803', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'The naturalist had argued that the island''s flightless birds lost flight because no predators forced them to flee. Critics countered that the birds'' ancestors arrived already capable of flight, and that flight is metabolically expensive to maintain. ______, abandoning it on a predator-free island would conserve energy rather than reflect mere disuse.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"Thus,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Thus draws the critics'' conclusion from the premise that flight is costly to maintain, yielding an energy-saving rationale."},{"id":"B","text":"However,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"However signals contrast, but the final sentence follows logically from the critics'' premise rather than opposing it."},{"id":"C","text":"Similarly,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Similarly marks a parallel case, but the sentence deduces a consequence rather than offering an analogous instance."},{"id":"D","text":"Granted,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Granted concedes a point to an opponent, but here the sentence completes the critics'' own argument."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step 1 — Find the premise
